Harware decription language (HDL)
- HDL is not another programming language
- Hardware construct that are all scattered around chip and execute in parallel
- textual representation of hardware construct
- all statement are executed in parallel
- code ordering is flexible, c=a+b; a=1; b=2
- execution of code is triggered by events
- sensitivity lists are used to define when a code section is executed
- different simulator may yield different results, coding style is required

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Abstraction levels
1) three coding style
 - structural code(GTL/gate level), netlist) 
 - RTL(register transfer level)
 - Behavioural(testbench)
2) DUT(device under test)
 - represent hardware
 - usually RTL or GTL
3) Testbench
 - represent system
 - usually behavioural
 - using high order language 

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Basic construct

1) Primitives : not,and, or   or(out,in1,in2);
2) signals
4 states : 0(ground voltage), 1(vdd voltage),x(error),z(high impedence state)
wires : do not keep states
registers : keep states (i.e output)
can represent buses or group of signal 

wire in1,in2;
reg out;
wire [7:0] data;
reg [31:0] mem [0:7]; width(bits) = 32, depth(words) = 8    8*32

3) operator 
&,|,~,&&,||   out = in1 | in2;
4) constants -> format is W'Bval (width, apostrophe,type,val)
1'b0 => 0 , b is binary
4'b0011 => 3

